Machining is manufacturing process that involves the removal of material from a workpiece to achieve the desired shape, size, and surface finish. It is a subtractive manufacturing method, meaning that material is removed from the workpiece to create the final product. The machine could be controlled by an operator (i.e., manual) or  by a Computer Numerical Control (i. e., CNC) system that can execute the instruction contained in a CAM program.

machining operation which consists of removing material by means of a rotary tool called a "milling cutter" of which there are several different types. Note 1 to entry: The typical milling operations mostly involve face milling or end milling. The tools are mounted either in the spindle taper or on the spindle front face. (ISO 8636-1:2000)
